    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Introduction"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "AUTOSAR OS is based upon the OSEK Operating System standard"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "OSEK - O ffene S ysteme und deren Schnittstellen für die E lektronik in K raftfahrzeugen →  In English \"Open Systems and their Interfaces for the Electronics in Motor Vehicles\""
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Architecture of the OSEK operating system"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "OSEK defines three processing levels:"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "Interrupt level",
        "Logical level for scheduler",
        "Task level"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/1.%20Autosar%20OS%20Introduction/image-2023-5-6_13-43-5.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/1. Autosar OS Introduction/image-2023-5-6_13-43-5.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "Priority Rules"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "Interrupts have precedence over tasks",
        "The interrupt processing level consists of one or more interrupt priority levels",
        "For task priorities and resource ceiling-priorities bigger numbers refer to higher priorities"
      ]
    }
  ],
